#Text=A Road Wanted Through Rannoch Proposal That Would Link East With West AN idea is taking shape to revive the proposed road from Rannoch to Glencoe .
#Text=It is just possible that the Highland District Council may have its attention drawn to the project soon .
#Text=Rannoch Station is a cul-de-sac .
#Text=From Kinloch-Rannoch the road runs alongside the loch to the station and ends there .
#Text=The plan is that the present road should be driven through across the Moor of Rannoch to join the Glencoe road near Kingshouse .
#Text=Meanwhile , as all walkers know , there is a path that runs along Loch Laidon to Kingshouse on the Glencoe road .
#Text=Here indeed , say the champions of the scheme , is the ideal site of the new carriage-way .
#Text=Ten Miles to Make .
#Text=ACTUALLY from Black Corries to Kingshouse there is a road - three miles in length .
#Text=Altogether there would be only about ten miles to make , and the gain to motorists and the district would be obvious , as a glance at the map will show .
#Text=With the opening of the new Glencoe Road the Rannoch district has felt draught .
#Text=Traffic has been diverted to the West Highlands for obvious reasons .
#Text=The motorist who goes along from Kinloch-Rannoch to Rannoch Station must turn and come back the same way , and motorists with fast cars and good roads are not built that way .
#Text=They want variety .
#Text=Some years ago the people of Rannoch took up the question , and sent a petition , which was signed by practically everybody in the neighbourhood , to the County Council .
#Text=It was felt then the time was inopportune , and the subject dropped .
#Text=The Benefit .
#Text=WITH the Ministry of Transport more disposed to consider road schemes , it is considered that the project might be put forward now .
#Text=Here is a short cut to the West Highlands .
#Text=One has only to look at the map to appreciate what is involved and the benefit to be derived .
#Text=East and West would be brought nearer .
#Text=From Pitlochry the route would be either by Struan and Kinloch-Rannoch or by Tummelside to Tummelbridge and straight through to Rannoch .
#Text=From Dundee , Perth , and Aberdeen it would provide a through road either to the West Highlands or even to Oban .
#Text=The Only Way .

#Text=THE only way at present to the West from the East is by either the Great North Road to Dalwhinnie or Newtonmore and over by Spean Bridge , or by Killin , Crianlarich , Tyndrum , and Glencoe to Ballachulish and Kinlochleven .
#Text=Probably we will hear more of the project soon .
#Text=This , after all , is a part of the old road to the Isles - by Tummel and Loch Rannoch .
#Text=
